para.computeroutput: 'Error Creating Child Task for CPU Utilization Monitoring,RC=0x%08X'
'Error Creating Child Task for CPU Utilization Monitoring,RC=0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when CFS Health and Safety is unable to create its child task via the CFE_ES_CreateChildTask API
The RC field contains the return status from the CFE_ES_CreateChildTask call that generated the error

para.computeroutput: 'Error Registering Sync Callback for CPU Utilization Monitoring,RC=0x%08X'
'Error Registering Sync Callback for CPU Utilization Monitoring,RC=0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event message is issued when CFS Health and Safety is unable to create its sync callback via the CFE_TIME_RegisterSynchCallback API
The RC field contains the return status from the CFE_TIME_RegisterSynchCallback call that generated the error.

para.computeroutput: 'Mask 0x%08X Base Time Ticks per Idle Ticks (frequency): %i(%i), %i(%i), %i(%i), %i(%i)'
'Mask 0x%08X Base Time Ticks per Idle Ticks (frequency): %i(%i), %i(%i), %i(%i), %i(%i)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is issued when CFS Health and Safety receives the HS_REPORT_DIAG_CC command.

The Mask field contains the current utilization diagnostics mask. The subsequent fields contain from lowest to fourth lowest, the time time ticks per idle ticks, and the number of times it occurred (in parentheses).

Type: Debug
Cause:
This event message is issued when CFS Health and Safety successfully processes the HS_SET_UTIL_PARAMS_CC command.
The Mult1, Div, and Mult2 fields contain the updated utilization parameters.

para.computeroutput: 'Utilization Parms Error: No parameter may be 0: Mult1: %d Div: %d Mult2: %d'
'Utilization Parms Error: No parameter may be 0: Mult1: %d Div: %d Mult2: %d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: Error
Cause:
This event message is issued when CFS Health and Safety fails to processes the HS_SET_UTIL_PARAMS_CC command. due to a 0 as at least one of the parameters.
The Mult1, Div, and Mult2 fields contain the utilization parameters from the command.

para.computeroutput: 'Utilization Diagnostics Mask has been set to %08X'
'Utilization Diagnostics Mask has been set to %08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: Debug
Cause:
This event message is issued when CFS Health and Safety successfully processes the HS_SET_UTIL_DIAG_CC command.
The Mask parameter contains the new mask value.

briefdescription.para: Initialize things needed for CPU Monitoring.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is intended to set up everything necessary for CPU Utilization Monitoring at application startup. Currently, this initializes the Idle Task, spawning the task itself, and creating a 1Hz sync callback to mark the idle time. It is called at the end of HS_AppInit . It may be updated to include other initializations, or modifications to already set parameters.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: CFE_SUCCESS will be returned if all creation was performed properly.

briefdescription.para: Clean up the functionality used for Utilization Monitoring.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is intended to clean up everything necessary for CPU Utilization Monitoring at application termination. Currently, this terminates the Idle Task, deleting the task itself, and uncreating the 1Hz sync callback that marks the idle time. It is called at the end of HS_AppMain if HS is exiting cleanly.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: Any resources that will not be cleaned up automatically be CFE need to be cleaned up in this function.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is used as a passthrough to call HS_MonitorUtilization but can be modified to monitor utilization differently. It is called during HS_ProcessMain every HS cycle.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: None

briefdescription.para: Stub function for Getting the Current Cycle Utilization.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function is used to inform the Monitor Utilization function of the current cycle utilization. It is called during HS_MonitorUtilization and should return a value between 0 and HS_UTIL_PER_INTERVAL_TOTAL.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: None

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This function allows for hs_custom.c to define custom commands. It will be called for any command code not already allocated to a Health and Safety command. If a custom command is found, then it is responsible for incrementing the command processed or command error counter as appropriate.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: If a command is found, this function MUST return CFE_SUCCESS, otherwise is must not return CFE_SUCCESS

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: This child task is started by the HS initialization process. It runs at the lowest priority on the system, incrementing a counter when all other tasks are idle. This counter is used to determine CPU Hogging (by being non-zero each cycle) and Utilization.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: None

briefdescription.para: Increment the CPU Utilization Tracker Counter.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Utility function that increments the CPU Utilization tracking counter, called by Idle Task. This counter is used to determine both utilization and CPU Hogging.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: None

briefdescription.para: Mark the CPU Utilization Tracker Counter.

simplesect.title: Description
simplesect.para: Utility function that marks the CPU Utilization tracking counter while saving the previous value to a variable for use in calculating CPU Utilization and hogging.

simplesect.title: Assumptions, External Events, and Notes:
simplesect.para: None
